Requirements:
1.  Qt 4.x or later. Qt may be downloaded from
    http://www.qtsoftware.com/downloads.
2.  PostgreSQL 7.4.x or later, SQLite 3.5.6 or later.
    PostgreSQL may be downloaded from http://www.postgresql.org/download and
    SQLite from http://www.sqlite.org/download.html.
3.  YAZ 2.1.53 or later.
    YAZ may be downloaded from http://www.indexdata.dk/yaz.
4.  A C++ compiler.

Qt 4.x Preparation (Unix):
1.  Please build Qt with the PostgreSQL driver, for example:
    ./configure -v -qt-sql-psql -I /usr/local/include/postgresql \
    -L /usr/local/lib/postgresql
2.  You may also build the driver as a plugin.

PostgreSQL Preparation:
1.  Create the xbook_db database via createdb xbook_db. This name is only a suggestion.
2.  Run createlang plpgsql -d xbook_db.
3.  Log into PostgreSQL and execute the postgresql_create_schema.sql script.
    (\i postgresql_create_schema.sql)

SQLite Preparation:
1.  Run sqlite3 -init sqlite_create_schema.sql biblioteq.db.

Building:
1.  Set the environment variables LD_LIBRARY_PATH, PATH, QMAKESPEC, and QTDIR
    accordingly.
2.  Update the appropriate project file, if necessary.
3.  Run qmake -o Makefile file.pro.
4.  Run make.

Installing (OS X):
1.  Double-click on the version-specific BiblioteQ package.

Installing (Unix):
1.  Create the directory /usr/local/biblioteq.
2.  Modify biblioteq.conf and copy it to /usr/local/biblioteq.
3.  Copy BiblioteQ to /usr/local/biblioteq.
4.  Copy icons.d to /usr/local/biblioteq/icons.d.
5.  Set the desired permissions on the aforementioned files.

Installing (Windows):
1.  Launch the version-specific BiblioteQ-Installer.exe.
